# Laravel 13 Rules for Cursor

For full agent operating instructions and knowledge layer navigation, see:
- [`AGENTS.md`](../AGENTS.md)
- [`agent/retrieval-guide.md`](../agent/retrieval-guide.md)
- [`agent/domain-routing-index.md`](../agent/domain-routing-index.md)

## Core Rules

- Follow PSR-12 with Laravel Pint formatting.
- Use `declare(strict_types=1)` in all PHP files.
- Use Laravel 13 PHP 8 attributes: `#[Table]`, `#[Fillable]`, `#[Hidden]`, `#[Casts]`.
- Organize by feature (`app/Modules/User/`), not by type (`app/Models/`).
- Use Actions for single-purpose operations, Services for orchestration.
- Use readonly DTOs for all data crossing boundaries.
- Follow Controller → Action → Service → Contract → Infrastructure flow.
- Always use constructor injection, never `app()` or `resolve()` in business code.
- Depend on contracts (interfaces), not concrete implementations.
- Use facades only for infrastructure concerns (Cache, Log, DB); inject contracts elsewhere.

## Testing Rules

- Use Pest 4 for all tests (Laravel 13 default).
- 80% feature tests, 20% unit tests.
- Use Laravel fakes (Http, Mail, Queue, Storage) over mocks.
- Write architecture tests to enforce conventions.

## Security Rules

- Every model must have `#[Fillable]` or `#[Guarded]`.
- Never pass `$request->all()` to `Model::create()`.
- Use Blade `{{ }}` escaping (never `{!! !!}` without sanitizing).
- Apply rate limiting to all API endpoints.

## Laravel 13 Specific

- PHP 8.3+ required.
- Pest 4 is first-class with PHP Attribute Output.
- Use Pest 4 browser testing (Playwright) as the recommended approach for browser tests.
- Queue jobs use `#[Connection]`, `#[Tries]`, `#[Timeout]` attributes.
